@startuml
' Author: Nicholas Irvine  GitHub https://github.com/SaladStik  LinkedIn https://www.linkedin.com/in/nicholas-irvine-303ab5284/
title Orbit Kubernetes Topology

' How the same services map onto Kubernetes. Only nginx is
' published, through a NodePort that kind maps to the host.

skinparam shadowing false

actor "Your laptop\nhttps://localhost" as host

node "kind cluster (3 nodes)" {
  frame "namespace: orbit" {
    component "nginx\n(Deployment)\nNodePort 30080/30443" as nginx
    component "ui\n(Deployment)" as ui
    component "auth\n(Deployment)" as auth
    component "node-gateway\n(Deployment)" as gw
    component "python-worker\n(Deployment)" as worker
    component "Debezium\n(KafkaConnect)" as dbz

    component "redis\n(Deployment)" as redis
    node "orbit-kafka\n(Strimzi, 3 pods)" as kafka
    database "postgres\n(StatefulSet + PVC)" as pg
  }
}

host --> nginx : host 80/443 -> NodePort 30080/30443

nginx --> ui
nginx --> auth
nginx --> gw : /api/jobs (command) + /ws
auth --> redis : sessions
gw --> kafka
gw --> pg : 'queued' + history (read model)
worker --> kafka
worker --> pg
pg --> dbz
dbz --> kafka

note bottom of nginx : The only exposed Service. NodePorts 30080/30443 map to host 80/443 and TLS lives here.
note bottom of kafka : Strimzi three pod KRaft quorum. See 07.

@enduml
